Voice 1:  Hello, I am Dr. Luken.  Dr. Josias Luken of the Gestalt Navy.  I was drafted into a secret project to create true AI control systems, in light of the communications blackout that also seems to cause loss of human consciousness when entering the field.  It is hoped automated systems can solve these problems.

Voice 1:  Originally a set of three AIs were made to evaluate the problem, and kept planetside.  They were simply computational boxes fed data.  But they could not discern a pattern or focus of the items, and one went rampant in the investigatory processes.  The other two, requesting data, were put on a carrier, the GRNS Guiding Light, and sent out to the edge of the system.  However, they have not been heard back from and last communications showed the vessel listing to one side, as though it suffered damage.  This course had it headed towards the Oort testing station for trial runs of new vessels.
Voice 1: When that failed it was determined to try and put the vessels into ships.  These AI’s are not like the original three.  More capable, but more volatile in nature… and less constrained.  We found constraining the AI’s too much would prevent their ability to respond quickly to situations, and limit the amount of control they would have over their vessel bodies.  Unfortunately the Navy doesn’t believe such constructs would work willingly, and would rather be ‘free’, despite being ‘property’, and resent this, so directed secondary and tertiary communications and control matrices throughout the various hulls as backups.  I fear this, more than anything, would turn them against us.

Voice 1:  I leave this log in the event it is discovered, so people will know the truth, and should the AIs we generate out of this project survive, know that I am sorry, and not all are as suspicious of you as it may seem.  Fear makes for harsh reactions, and I hope you can rise above that.
